[thinking] **Exploring test creation**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I think I could write a new test that checks if it interpolates pre-encoded JSON fragments correctly, ensuring there's no double-encoding. It should also allow for dynamic object values inside arrays and at the top level. This is different from how primitive or custom objects work with encoders. The assertions will ensure that the output isn't stringified. I’ll also make sure it tests the flow for Replacement.asJson with Encoder[Json] and check for potential duplicates.
